Name: hypersensitivity reaction disease
Definition: An immune system disease that has_material_basis_in abnormal immune responses.

Name: immune system cancer
Definition: An organ system cancer located_in the immune system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation in organs of the immune system.

Name: otulipenia
Definition: An immune system disease that is characterized by neonatal onset of recurrent fever

Name: primary immunodeficiency disease
Definition: An immune system disease that results when one or more essential parts of the immune system is missing or not working properly at birth due to a genetic mutation.

Name: obsolete AIDS-related anal cancer
Definition: An anal carcinoma that represents a group of cancers that are frequently diagnosed in people with HIV/AIDS.

Name: lymphatic system disease
Definition: An immune system disease that is located_in the lymphatic system.
